# Accepted, non-reachable vulnerabilities for the container scan.
# Format: one vulnerability ID per line (https://trivy.dev/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/).
# Each entry must state the justification and a review date, and be removed as
# soon as an upstream fix is available in our pinned base image.

# CVE-2026-12151 (HIGH, CVSS 7.5) — undici WebSocket-client denial of service:
# a malicious WebSocket *server* can exhaust memory in a connecting undici
# client. Fixed in undici >= 6.27.0.
#   - Source: this is the undici copy bundled inside Node itself
#     (node:26.4.0-alpine ships undici 6.26.0). It is NOT an npm dependency we
#     can bump, and no Node release/alpine image yet ships undici >= 6.27.0.
#   - Reachability: NONE. TL-Finance opens no undici WebSocket client
#     connections (it uses SMTP via nodemailer and outbound HTTP only); the
#     vulnerable WebSocket-client code path is never executed.
#   - Action: remove this entry once a Node alpine image bundles undici
#     >= 6.27.0. Review by 2026-09-01.
CVE-2026-12151
